# Race Condition in Async Map

Found a race condition when using `Promise.all(items.map(async item => ...))` where each callback modified a shared counter/array.

## Problem
```javascript
// BUG: Race condition — shared `results` array gets corrupted
let results = [];
await Promise.all(items.map(async (item) => {
  const processed = await processItem(item);
  results.push(processed); // Multiple concurrent pushes
}));
```

## Fix
```javascript
// Option 1: Use map return values (no shared mutation)
const results = await Promise.all(items.map(async (item) => {
  return await processItem(item);
}));

// Option 2: Sequential when order matters
const results = [];
for (const item of items) {
  results.push(await processItem(item));
}
```

## Lesson
Never mutate shared state inside `Promise.all(map(...))`. Either use the return values of the mapped promises, or iterate sequentially if side effects are needed.
